a]]\n|[[Andhra Pradesh]]\n|{{small|{{coord|14|01|N|78|26|E|name=NP Kunta Ultra Mega Solar Power Project}}}}\n|{{nts|500}}\n|2018\n|In [[Nambulapulakunta]] Mandal. Total planned capacity 1500 MW\n|<ref>[http://www.indiainfoline.com/article/news-top-story/ntpc-commissioned-50-mw-of-np-kunta-ultra-mega-solar-power-project-stage-i-in-anantapuramu-116080100328_1.html NTPC commissioned 50 MW of NP Kunta Ultra Mega Solar Power Project Stage-I in Anantapuramu] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170304200105/http://www.indiainfoline.com/article/news-top-story/ntpc-commissioned-50-mw-of-np-kunta-ultra-mega-solar-power-project-stage-i-in-anantapuramu-116080100328_1.html|date=2017-03-04}}, India Infoline News Service, August 01, 2016</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://mercomindia.com/solar-projects-127-commissioning-may/|title=Solar Projects Totaling 127 MW Commissioned This Week|access-date=23 May 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180524081718/https://mercomindia.com/solar-projects-127-commissioning-may/|archive-date=24 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/tata-power-commissions-100-mw-solar-power-capacity-in-ap-118070200548_1.html|title=Tata Power commissions 100 MW solar power capacity in AP|access-date=3 July 2018|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702114519/https://www.business-standard.com/article/pti-stories/tata-power-commissions-100-mw-solar-power-capacity-in-ap-118070200548_1.html|archive-date=2 July 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|Ananthapuramu - II\n|[[Andhra Pradesh]]\n|{{small|{{coord|14|58|49|N|78|02|45|E|name=Ananthapuramu II solar park}}}}\n|{{nts|400}}\n|2019\n|Located at Talaricheruvu village in [[Tadipatri]] mandal of [[Anantapur district]]. Planned capacity 500 MW\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/solar-plant-commissioned/article26315321.ece|title=Solar plant commissioned|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web