rin J. Crane ('''k'''), Cpt Ernst J. Krieger\n*[[29th Ohio Infantry|29th Ohio]]: Col William F. Fitch\n*[[66th Ohio Infantry|66th Ohio]]: Ltc Eugene Powell, Cpt Thomas McConnell\n*[[28th Pennsylvania Infantry|28th Pennsylvania]]: Col Thomas J. Ahl, Cpt John H. Flynn\n*[[147th Pennsylvania Infantry|147th Pennsylvania]]: Ltc [[Ario Pardee, Jr.]]\n|-\n| 2nd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[George A. Cobham, Jr.]]\n|\n*[[29th Pennsylvania Infantry|29th Pennsylvania]]: Col William Rickards, Jr.\n*[[109th Pennsylvania Infantry|109th Pennsylvania]]: Cpt Frederick L. Gimber\n*[[111th Pennsylvania Infantry|111th Pennsylvania]]: Col Thomas M. Walker\n|-\n| 3rd Brigade\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nCol [[David Ireland (colonel)|David Ireland]]\n|\n*[[60th New York Volunteer Infantry|60th New York]]: Col [[Abel Godard]]\n*[[78th New York Volunteer Infantry|78th New York]]: Ltc Herbert von Hammerstein\n*[[102nd New York Volunteer Infantry|102nd New York]]: Col James C. Lane\n*[[137th New York Volunteer Infantry|137th New York]]: Cpt Milo B. Eldredge\n*[[149th New York Volunteer Infantry Regiment|149th New York]]: Col [[Henry A. Barnum]],<ref>Relinquished command on account of sickness (''see: Randoll's report'')</ref> Ltc Charles B. Randoll\n|-\n| Artillery\n<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;\nMaj John A. Reynolds<ref>Chief of Artillery, Twelfth Corps</ref>\n|\n*[[Independent Battery E, Pennsylvania Light Artillery|Pennsylvania Light Artillery, Battery E]]: Lt James D. McGill\n*[[5th U.S. Light Artillery, Battery K|5th United States, Battery K]]: Cpt Edmund C. Bainbridge\n|}\n\n===[[Army of the Tennessee]]===\nMG [[William Tecumseh Sherman|William T. Sherman]]<ref>General Sherman had under his immediate command the Eleventh Corps and the Second Division, Fourteenth Corps, of the Army of the Cumberland; the Second and Fourth Divisions, Fifteenth Corps.</ref>\n\n====[[XV Corps (Union Army)|XV Corps]]====\nMG [[Francis P. Blair, Jr.|Francis P. Blair]]<ref>The Third Division, Brigadier General James M. Tuttle c